      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0030",
      "text": "Read Exchange Concise (REC)",
      "bbox": [
        133.82,
        358.96,
        280.45,
        370.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0031",
      "text": "4.2.42.1  Description",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        382.96,
        192.63,
        394.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0032",
      "text": "This ELS shall be used only for purposes specific to an FC-4.  The REC (Read Exchange Concise)",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        406.96,
        539.99,
        418.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0033",
      "text": "Extended Link Service requests an Nx_Port to return Exchange information for the RX_ID and",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        418.96,
        539.87,
        430.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0034",
      "text": "OX_ID originated by the S_ID specified in the Payload of the request Sequence.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        430.96,
        450.42,
        442.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0035",
      "text": "A Read Exchange Concise Request shall only be accepted if the Originator Nx_Port N_Port_ID or",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        454.96,
        539.97,
        466.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0036",
      "text": "the Responder Nx_Port N_Port_ID of the target Exchange is the same as the N_Port_ID of the",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        466.96,
        540.03,
        478.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0037",
      "text": "Nx_Port that makes the request. If the REC Request is not accepted, an LS_RJT with reason code",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        478.96,
        539.97,
        490.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0038",
      "text": "\"Unable to perform command request\" and reason code explanation \"Invalid Originator S_ID\" shall",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        490.96,
        539.98,
        502.07
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0039",
      "text": "be returned.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        502.96,
        149.86,
        514.07
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0040",
      "text": "The specification of OX_ID and RX_ID shall be provided for the destination Nx_Port to locate the sta-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        526.96,
        540.1,
        538.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0041",
      "text": "tus information requested.  A Responder destination Nx_Port shall use the RX_ID and verify that the",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        538.96,
        539.96,
        550.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0042",
      "text": "OX_ID is consistent, unless the RX_ID is unassigned (i.e., RX_ID = FFFFh).  If the RX_ID is unas-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        550.96,
        539.95,
        562.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0043",
      "text": "signed in the request, the Responder shall identify the Exchange by means of the S_ID specified in",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        562.96,
        539.89,
        574.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0044",
      "text": "the Payload of the request Sequence and OX_ID.  An Originator Nx_Port shall use the OX_ID and",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        574.96,
        539.95,
        586.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0045",
      "text": "verify that the RX_ID is consistent.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        586.96,
        248.81,
        598.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0046",
      "text": "If the destination Nx_Port of the REC request determines that the Originator S_ID, OX_ID, or RX_ID",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        610.96,
        540.01,
        622.07
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0047",
      "text": "are inconsistent, then it shall reply with an LS_RJT Sequence with a reason code of \"Unable to per-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        622.96,
        540.09,
        634.07
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0048",
      "text": "form command request\" and a reason code explanation of \"Invalid OX_ID-RX_ID combination\".",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        634.96,
        516.52,
        646.07
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0049",
      "text": "The value of the Parameter field in the frame header of an REC ELS and an LS_ACC in response to",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        659.02,
        540.02,
        670.13
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0050",
      "text": "an REC ELS shall be specified by the FC-4 that sends the frame.  The Relative offset present bit in",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        671.02,
        539.95,
        682.13
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p127_s0051",
      "text": "the frame header of an REC ELS or an LS_ACC in response to an REC ELS shall be set to zero.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        683.02,
        524.16,
        694.13
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    }
  ],
